17:
WHAT?!
Oh, it's just you two.
18:
You fishing? Not a bad haul you got
there.
22:
You're not here just to laugh at us,
right?
24:
Do I look like I've got that much free
time?
Hey, if you're ready to give up for the
day, I could use some help shopping.
26:
Show that to the local pharmacist.
He should have everything in stock.
30:
Research materials...
I think you had best go yourself. To
guard against any confusion.
33:
It's a pain, putting on a disguise. And
I hate it when people freak out
about my tail.
36:
Saar, there are beastfolk in this
world. And in the eyes of your
people, Nimbus and I must appear
as strange, if not stranger than you.
38: ...I don't like being on land, okay?
39:
Just do me this favor. I'll be waiting
here.
48:
By the way, I took the liberty of filling
your bucket.
53:
That takes care of dinner. You have
our gratitude, Saar.
57:
Hey, why don't you eat with us
tonight? I'm accepting requests.
61:
I told you I don't do well on land.
Your floating island is no exception.
65:
I could also cook at your place. Did
you have a kitchen?
68:
I've got a stove, but uh... I only use it
to refine poisons.
74:
Wait. There aren't any merfolk
around.
76:
...You needed them to breathe
underwater, right?
90:
Yeah, made from my cells. Have you
breathing underwater for several
hours.
103:
Do you understand the greatness of
your own research?
107: Don't get your tail in a knot!
108:
Like I said, I'm researching my
identity. Stumbled on that formula
by accident.
110:
Anyways, doesn't matter! What I
wanna know is, are you feeding me
or not?!
